// D1 cartridge registry for the LabelManager driver.
//
// Ported from the labelwriter D1 worksheet
// (../../../../labelwriter/plans/backlog/media-registry-d1.csv) so the
// two drivers carry the same SKUs and colour metadata. The plan covers
// the cross-driver shared shape; per the plan §4 each driver owns its
// own copy of this list rather than depending on a shared package.
//
// Supported widths today: 6 / 9 / 12 / 19 mm. The CSV's 24 mm entries
// are deliberately omitted — the LabelManager rasterizer caps at the
// 64-dot transport path (see `tapeWidthToHeadDots` in src/protocol.ts),
// so 24 mm cartridges cannot be driven correctly even on chassis that
// physically accept them. Land them with `targetModels: ['d1-wide']`
// when the rasterizer learns to address more than 64 dots; the
// wide-capable engine entries gain `mediaCompatibility: ['d1', 'd1-wide']`
// at the same time. See ../../plans/backlog/wide-tier-media-compatibility.md.
//
// Driver-side fields beyond the contracts `MediaDescriptor` shape:
//   - `material`   — D1 substrate family (standard / permanent-polyester /
//                    flexible-nylon / durable / rhino-*). Picker UX hint.
//   - `text`       — printed colour, named (the only ink the cartridge
//                    carries). Mirrors the CSV column.
//   - `background` — substrate colour, named. Mirrors the CSV column.
//
// `printableDots` and `bytesPerLine` per width match the existing
// `tapeWidthToHeadDots` cap: 6→32/4, 9→48/6, 12→64/8, 19→64/8.
//
// ─── Rhino™ industrial cartridges (rhino-*) ──────────────────────
// DYMO's Rhino industrial line uses cartridges that are mechanically
// the same shape as D1 and physically fit LabelManager chassis;
// community reports (silvenga.com/posts/tip-dymo-label-compatibility,
// dymo-label-printers.co.uk FAQ) corroborate the cross-fit. DYMO does
// not officially endorse the cross-use, and the stiffer industrial
// substrates — heat-shrink polyolefin and durable polyester
// especially — accelerate cutter blade and motor wear over time.
// Project assumes no responsibility for wear, damage, or warranty
// implications. See HARDWARE.md for the user-facing disclaimer.
//
// SKUs below transcribed from the official DYMO Industrial Labels
// datasheet (en, 2011 ref printing — colours and SKU codes have been
// stable since). The 24mm Rhino entries are deliberately omitted for
// the same reason as standard 24mm D1 — see the cap-lift comment
// above. Self-laminating Rhino is 24mm-only and is therefore absent
// in its entirety here.
[
  // ─── 6 mm — Standard ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  {
    id: 'd1-standard-bw-6',
    name: '6mm Black on White (D1)',
    widthMm: 6,
    type: 'tape',
    category: 'cartridge',
    targetModels: ['d1'],
    defaultOrientation: 'horizontal',
    printMargins: { leftMm: 3, rightMm: 3, topMm: 0, bottomMm: 0 },
    skus: ['43613', 'S0720780'],
    material: 'standard',
    text: 'black',
    background: 'white',
    tapeWidthMm: 6,
    printableDots: 32,
    bytesPerLine: 4,
  },

